{{Han etym}}
According to ''{{w|Shuowen}}'', an {{Han compound|人|更|alt1=亻|ls=ic|t1=person|t2=to change|nocap=y}} – to change one's posture to make oneself comfortable.

Alternatively, this may be the original character for {{och-l|鞭|to whip}}, from {{Han compound|人|𠓥|t1=person|t2=whip}}, as seen in the bronze script.

